OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas feasible, papers show
OL,6,FIt threatened to introduce weed killer
OL,7,Finto the water supply in England
OL,8,Funless the British Government
OL,9,Fannounced its intention to withdraw
OL,10,Ffrom "occupied Ireland" by the
OL,11,Ffollowing day.
OL,13,FThe letters said an improvised
OL,14,Fchemical weapon would be attached to
OL,15,Ffire hydrants in England, forcing the
OL,16,Fchemical ` a commonly available
OL,17,Fweedkiller called "New Pathclear" `
OL,18,Finto the water supply, potentially
OL,19,Fpoisoning hundreds of thousands of
OL,20,Fpeople.
