OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas feasible, papers show
OL,6,FAlthough the threat might appear far-
OL,7,Ffetched, the British authorities took
OL,8,Fit seriously because the technical
OL,9,Fprocesses had been checked and were
OL,10,Ffeasible, because the threatening
OL,11,Fletter was "cohesive and literate",
OL,12,Fand because it had been sent to the
OL,13,Fright people in the UK, including the
OL,14,Fappropriate water authorities.
OL,16,FHowever, the British Embassy in Dublin
OL,17,Fthought the letter might be a dirty
OL,18,Ftrick by loyalists designed to smear
OL,19,Frepublicans.
