OL,3,CThreat to poison English water supply
OL,4,Cwas feasible, papers show
OL,6,FThe potential giveaway was references
OL,7,Fto "HMG" (Her Majesty's Government)
OL,8,Fthroughout the threat, a phrase
OL,9,Funlikely to be used in earnest by a
OL,10,Frepublican.
OL,12,FThe authorities decided they had to
OL,13,Ftake the threat seriously in the
OL,14,Fcircumstances, even though it was
OL,15,Fthought the risk to life was low.
OL,17,FMost people who drank contaminated
OL,18,Fwater would suffer nothing worse than
OL,19,Fa stomach upset, though it could
OL,20,Fthreaten the lives of babies, and of
OL,21,Fpeople on dialysis.
